## How Much Should a Website Cost for a Small Business in South Wales?

Whether you're a tradesperson, startup, or independent service provider, having a website is no longer optional — it's essential. At [NC Digital](/), we've built websites for businesses across South Wales and know one of the most common questions is: "How much should it cost?"

While there's no one-size-fits-all price, we aim to make things as transparent and affordable as possible. **We build lean, effective websites** that work hard for small businesses — without inflated agency costs.

> "A good website doesn't have to break the bank — it just needs to be built with purpose."
> NC Digital

#### What Affects the Cost of a Website?

Every business is different, but a few key factors influence cost:

- How many pages you need (we recommend 5 for a starter site)
- If you need extra functionality like forms, bookings, or e-commerce
- Whether you're supplying content and images, or need help with that too

**At NC Digital,** our starter package begins from **£600**, which includes a 5-page WordPress website, mobile optimisation, and on-page SEO setup.

#### What's Included in Our Starter Sites?

- Clean, mobile-friendly design (looks great on phones and desktops)
- Built on [WordPress](https://wordpress.org/) for full access and easy updates
- SEO-ready setup to help you appear on [Google](https://www.google.com/)
- Secure UK hosting & SSL certificate included for the first year

#### How We Keep Costs Down

We're not a huge agency with account managers and overheads — we're a small team based in Merthyr Tydfil, working closely with local businesses. That means you get real value, quicker turnarounds, and honest advice.

